From: 3090 team <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: 2026-06-10
Subject: [PATCH] qwen3_5: enable text-only CausalLM checkpoints (CT mirrors)

Merged unit (2026-06-10) absorbing former 035-qwen3_5-causal-lm-entry-class
(2026-05-19) + 036-qwen3_5-layer-types-hf-fallback (2026-05-19) +
038-qwen3_5-norm-topk-prob-fallback (v0.5.12 rebase). One enablement chain
for checkpoints declaring Qwen3_5(Moe)ForCausalLM (our CT-format mirrors):
(1) register both CausalLM heads in qwen3_5.py EntryClass (they were
implemented but not exposed -> "has no SGLang implementation");
(2) get_layer reads layers_block_type (sglang config) OR layer_types
(HF config wins AutoConfig lookup for model_type qwen3_5_moe_text) and
translates full_attention->attention; (3) qwen2_moe TopK falls back to
norm_topk_prob=True when the Qwen3.5/3.6 text config omits the attr.
Steps 2+3 are meaningless without 1; 1 crashes without 2+3.
Per-member narratives: patches/README.md.

diff --git a/python/sglang/srt/models/qwen2_moe.py b/python/sglang/srt/models/qwen2_moe.py
index 8bdc0598e..695f060f1 100644
--- a/python/sglang/srt/models/qwen2_moe.py
+++ b/python/sglang/srt/models/qwen2_moe.py
@@ -248,7 +248,11 @@ class Qwen2MoeSparseMoeBlock(nn.Module):
 
         self.topk = TopK(
             top_k=config.num_experts_per_tok,
-            renormalize=config.norm_topk_prob,
+            # Qwen3.5/3.6 (Qwen3_5MoeTextConfig) omit norm_topk_prob and reuse
+            # this qwen2_moe block; default True (Qwen MoE family renormalizes
+            # top-k — matches observed wsum=1). Qwen2 configs carry the real
+            # attr so getattr is a no-op for them. [3090 0.5.12 rebase]
+            renormalize=getattr(config, "norm_topk_prob", True),
             layer_id=layer_id,
         )
 
diff --git a/python/sglang/srt/models/qwen3_5.py b/python/sglang/srt/models/qwen3_5.py
index 7e5a68e06..b534d9b6a 100644
--- a/python/sglang/srt/models/qwen3_5.py
+++ b/python/sglang/srt/models/qwen3_5.py
@@ -1054,7 +1054,16 @@ class Qwen3_5ForCausalLM(nn.Module):
 
         # Decoder layers
         def get_layer(idx: int, prefix: str):
-            layer_type = config.layers_block_type[idx]
+            # sglang's Qwen3NextConfig exposes `layers_block_type` via @property
+            # with values "attention" / "linear_attention". HF transformers'
+            # Qwen3_5MoeTextConfig (which AutoConfig picks for the bare causal LM
+            # route — sglang's qwen3_5 configs never call AutoConfig.register)
+            # only has `layer_types` with HF's values "full_attention" /
+            # "linear_attention". Read either, normalize to sglang's keys.
+            layer_type_list = getattr(config, "layers_block_type", None) or config.layer_types
+            layer_type = layer_type_list[idx]
+            if layer_type == "full_attention":
+                layer_type = "attention"
             layer_class = ALL_DECODER_LAYER_TYPES[layer_type]
             if layer_type == "attention":
                 prefix = add_prefix("self_attn", prefix)
@@ -2086,4 +2095,9 @@ class Qwen3_5MoeForConditionalGeneration(Qwen3VLForConditionalGeneration):
         )
 
 
-EntryClass = [Qwen3_5MoeForConditionalGeneration, Qwen3_5ForConditionalGeneration]
+EntryClass = [
+    Qwen3_5MoeForConditionalGeneration,
+    Qwen3_5MoeForCausalLM,
+    Qwen3_5ForConditionalGeneration,
+    Qwen3_5ForCausalLM,
+]
